data.description: Price reduced...You don’t find homes like this vey often.. come tour this 4 bedroom/ 2.1 bath colonial situated on a scenic four acre lot. As you approach this wonderful home, you will appreciate the amazing curb appeal this home offers with the circle driveway, spacious brick patio overlooking the grounds and tennis/ pickleball/sport- utility court. The main floor offers the custom kitchen with granite countertops,  upgraded cabinets, farmhouse sink, double oven and hardwood floors. The kitchen flows directly into the breakfast area and separate formal dining room. The kitchen also leads into the bright & sunny solarium that offers amazing views of the grounds and wildlife. The main floor includes the family room with sliding doors to the patio and double sided wood burning fireplace from the dining room. The family room flows into the separate “Bar area” with built in bar and lounge area. The main floor also offers a spacious formal living room and updated half bath. The 2nd floor includes the full hall bathroom, three guest bedrooms, full bonus room - walk in closet and the main bedroom suite that offers a private bathroom and private home office. You will absolutely love the outdoor living space and grounds this home offers. You have a large brick patio to enjoy the sunsets, outbuildings for storage and the tennis/pickleball/utility court to play and entertain on. For those of you who prefer a scenic setting and outdoor living, this home is for you. This home is located just minutes from the popular Green Lane Reservoir   offering a variety of year-round, outdoor activities and programs for people to choose from. Park visitors can enjoy fishing, boating (including boat rentals), family and group camping, picnicking, 25 miles of trails for horseback riding, mountain biking and hiking, as well as two children's playgrounds. Winter enthusiasts can cross-country ski, ice fish or go ice skating. The park also offers summer concerts and environmental education programs on weekends.
